Thailand Stocks: Bangchak Petroleum, Pruksa, Khon Kaen Sugar

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-06-15T03:55:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/khon-kaen-precious-total-access-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:43 a.m. in Bangkok.  The SET Index fell 3.41, or 0.3 percent, to 1,031.51.  Pruksa Real Estate Pcl (PS)  , Thailand’s second-largest
property developer, declined 1.1 percent to 17.7 baht on concern
that accelerating inflation may curb  consumer spending  and boost
 interest rates . The Bank of Thailand said oil and food prices
remained at high levels, putting pressure on inflation,
according to the minutes of its June 1 meeting.  Bangchak Petroleum Pcl (BCP)  , a state-controlled oil
refiner, climbed 2.5 percent to 20.5 baht. The Stock Exchange of
Thailand will add Bangchak’s shares to the SET50 Index from July
1, the bourse said in a statement.  Khon Kaen Sugar Industry Pcl (KSL)  , the bigger of two
publicly traded sugar millers, gained 1.5 percent to 14 baht.
The company expects net profit will climb to a record this year
as global sugar prices surge, Post Today reported, citing Chief
Executive Officer Chamroon Chinthammit. Chamroon wasn’t
available for comment after a call to his office. Bualuang
Securities Pcl raised Khon Kaen’s share-price estimate to 16.5
baht from 16 baht, citing a surge in its quarterly net income.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at  
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 